<Content>Cheap and ok. My partner and i stayed here when we spent a week in Hong Kong in April before going to Thailand. We chose the hotel because it looked good value for money. Our view was we didnt want to pay a lot for a hotel that we did not intend to do more than sleep in. That is who this hotel is good for, dont expect full luxury. The hotel is away for the very touristy areas of Hong Kong, it was within easy walking distance of the harbour and other attractions (as most things are in Hong Kong). The hotel itself was nice, the lobby was very clean and was always busy, the staff were helpful. The room was very clean with good air con, the bed was large and firm. I only have one complaint about the hotel and that was its location, it is very close to the fish packing district. This isnt a problem in the hotel itself but if you wish to walk anywhere rather than get a taxi it can get quite smelly especially in the hot weather. Apart from one very noisy night due to business men in the next room, which i complained about and the staff sorted out, a nice hotel and we would probably use it again if we were on a budget just passing through Hong Kong. 
