<Author>skyline22usa
<Content>Love and hate Ramada I am a native Hong Konger. This hotel is in Kennedy Town where I was born. so I thought it would be nice to stay there for old time sake. Turned out the room was nice and clean. It is the only good thing about this hotel. I got a good rate for this hotel back in 2005, that's why it wasn't so bad. If you are paying 2008 price, I would not stay there at all. Why?Bad location. It is at the west end of Hong Kong island, truly a residential area. No subway, very inconvenient. Every night, we had to either take the subway to Sheung Wan and then took another tram ride to get to the hotel or we would take mini-bus from Causeway Bay. It was ok the first couple of days but it got tiresome. If you are not Chinese, cannot speak or read Chinese, you may have a tough time figuring out the transportation. Taxi is not cheap in Hong Kong. Traffic is always bad. For the same cost, you can find decent hotels in more convenient locations. The rooms may not be as big or new as Ramada but you won't feel like you are wasting a lot of time commuting.That said. You can find lots of cheap places to eat in the neighborhood. Mostly local Hong Kong style cooking, yummy.I would not stay there again because of the bad location. 
