<Author>Dominique_SF
<Content>Wonderful base to explore Hong Kong My parents are originally from Hong Kong so this trip for me was not the typical vacation (I spent most summers as a child staying with my uncles in Hong Kong and am quite familiar with the city).I loved this hotel because it's located in a very authentic part of Hong Kong...not the glitzy high rises of TST or Central, rather it reminded me of my uncles' old places. There were so many practical amenities around the hotel...breakfast places for 40HK for two; bakeries; laundry stalls. I loved the atmosphere and got to practice my Cantonese, but if you're not comfortable in non-Western settings then I wouldn't recommend it.The hotel itself was a fairly standard-issue chain hotel, though the rooms were nicer / larger than I expected. Because our room wasn't ready when we arrived we were upgraded to a suite...palatial by Hong Kong standards. It was a real steal for us since we booked the rooms for just $100USD per night and we ended up with a 300+ sq foot suite with a separate dining / seating area. It wasn't fancy but was a very comfortable home base for a week's trip. The only disappointment was the gym...really only a tiny, hot, dank room with a flimsy bike and treadmill.Bottom line is if you're comfortable staying a little outside the busiest areas and want to experience the real Hong Kong and get a great deal on a room...then the Ramada is it. 
